1. About me

Salutations to you.

My name is Joseph, and I specialize in data scraping, formatting, and analysis, as well as making small automation scripts with AI integration.

Sadly, it doesn't end there; I also have an interest in: typography, color, writing, business world, music instruments, tech, philosophy, and psychology.

I am always seeking a team, where a misfit like me can be useful across multiple areas.

2.1. Project 1

Sunken businesses on Google map

Preview:

As I was scraping Google map I discover that 2.7% of all records I have, are of businesses located in the middle of the sea; out of these 2.7%, 73% businesses share the same coordinates [46.423669, -129.9427086]

2.7. Project 7

Serve your customer with your own data

Preview:

This project utilizes the RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary Value) model to enhance marketing strategies for different customer segments.
Customer Examples

  • Customer A: Recently shopped, purchased 10 items, spent $250.
  • Customer B: Last shopped long ago, purchased 2 items, spent $1,000.

Marketing Strategies

For Customer A, we will send coupons to encourage repeat purchases. For Customer B, who has a history of buying high-value items, we will showcase our new line of premium products to re-engage them effectively. This targeted approach ensures relevant communications that drive sales.
